  "title": "Graduate Officer, Financial Institutions",
  "description": "<p>Report to Head of Financial Institutions (FI) and assist the team in:</p><ul><li>FI customer and counterparty acquisition and access</li><li>Managing correspondent banking activities including Nostro and Vostro accounts, SWIFT relationship management application and its correspondences</li><li>Market and monitor FI Trade Finance business with credible counterparties in both Singapore and China market</li><li>Market FI products</li><li>FI credit line management, liaising between HO, sister branches and our departments</li><li>FI credit application and credit review preparation</li><li>Perform customer due diligence measures as and when\nnecessary</li><li>ad-hoc task</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Recent graduates with a Bachelor's degree from reputable Universities</li><li>Strong interest in front office roles and eagerness to learn</li><li>Strong analytical skills, attention to detail and problem solving skills</li><li>Good communication skills both verbal and written with ability to interact comfortably with a variety of stakeholders</li><li>Ability to work effectively, independently and as part of a team</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office</li><li>Proficient in English and Chinese languages as the incumbent is required to correspond with our clients and colleagues in both English and Chinese (spoken and written)</li></ul>",
